This analysis detects pointer offset usage before negative/bounds validation.
1. Where is the pointer dereference or offset access performed?
2. Where is the corresponding offset range check, and does it dominate all paths?
3. Can untrusted or unchecked offset values reach the access site first?
4. Could negative or oversized offsets trigger out-of-bounds behavior?
Use the tools to trace full control flow from input to access and check.
If all reachable paths validate offset before access, there is no issue.
Only flag if at least one reachable path uses offset before validation.
